<br />Even new-in-box hardware manufactured in the past two years might not necessarily be capable of running bsnes at full speed. Case in point: Acer's Aspire Revo, ASUS's Eee Box, and other small, quiet PCs with an Atom CPU and an NVIDIA ION chipset. Now ION has a GeForce 9400 GPU, which can run CUDA- and OpenCL-accelerated decoders, making it ideal for watching AVC video on your HDTV. But then someone gets the bright idea to try playing 20-year-old video games on the PC that happens to be already connected to the TV, and its Atom CPU becomes a liability, as <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=60693#60693" class="postlink">kyuusaku discovered</a>.

		

